{"_id":"97enBRTlp4rorDQU","name":"Medium Body Armor","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p><strong>Medium Body Armor&nbsp;(Core Rules, pg 76)</strong></p>\n<div title=\"Page 78\">\n<p>Less protection than Heavy Body Armor, more than Light Body Armor - this sort of armor is often employed by elite security or police SWAT teams. What it lacks in protection it makes up for in better speed and mobility (Defense) offering a good compromise for when you're not expecting to face a particularly well armed opponent.</p>\n<p><strong>UNN Standard Armor </strong>is an example of typical Medium Body Armor</p>\n<p>The United Nations Navy utilizes two types of light armor for its armed forces.</p>\n<h4><strong>Type I</strong></h4>\n<p>This variant of light armor is utilized by the United Nations Marine Corps and by UN Military Police. It is worn over the standard uniform of the Marine Corps. It consists of a standard chest piece with provides armor whilst retaining flexibility, along with armor on the lower arms, upper arms, and thighs. This armor can be worn with UN VAC suit.</p>\n<p>A riot-police version also exists consisting of the chest-piece and a separate helmet.</p>\n<p>Several security firms such as Star Helix Security and CPM also use the chest piece of this armor for riot control.</p>\n<p>Unlike Martian Leviathn Combar Armor this armor is not part of VAC suit as standard, but can be attached.</p>\n<h4><strong>Type II</strong></h4>\n<p>This armor is utilized solely by the United Nations Marine Corps. It is a fully enclosed armor that provides full body armor and is compatible with an enclosed Helmet.</p>\n<p>The armor has an inbuilt computer on its wrists, and contains a holster for pistols on the right thigh.</p>\n<p>Marines onboard Truman-class dreadnoughts wear this armor and several whilst equipped in it provided security onboard the Behemoth during the slow zone incident.</p>\n<p>This armor is the equivalent of the Martian Leviathan Combat Armor in most functions. This armor however is noticeably bulkier than the Martian armor.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":"14","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":4,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":4,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":null,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"str":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.97enBRTlp4rorDQU"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.rSVJBsj6BtkTDa1b"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/Task_Force_Police_officer_in_Sweden.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9ULytiQl5lii7u7G","name":"Leviathan Combat Suit","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p><strong>Leviathan Combat Suit</strong></p>\n<p>Ex-Martian combat armor:&nbsp;&nbsp;Vaccuum-rated, +1 Accuracy, +1 against environment-based Hazard Checks, +1 to checks agasint DEX (Freefall). Note: Wearing this armor does not confer the DEX (Freefall) focus to the wearer, but it does afford a bonus to such checks if the wearer has that focus.</p>\n<p>Leviathan Combat armor is the primary armor worn by the Martian Marine Corps. Like those of the UNN, it combines both vacuum capabilities and armor protection as standard. The medium armor is functional as both a vacuum suit and for general body protection even on Earth, if visiting there on a Martian embassy detail.</p>\n<p>Specs</p>\n<p>The armor covers the torso and all limbs while retaining flexibility to allow the wearer good movement. Inbuilt into both wrists are holographic computers which can be used to scan DNA via the fingertip. The armor also contains thrusters for maneuvering when in zero-g environments.</p>\n<p>There are two variants of helmet worn with this armor, the 1st variant with increased face armor, and 2nd variant with a full-face panel. Both helmets include a sun-visor that can be pulled down over the face panels. Both Marines and Navy personnel can wear this armor.</p>\n<p>Air for vacuum operation is provided by a backpack which can be attached. For rapid decelerating an expendable thruster pack ejects from the backpack and provides downwards thrust for a few moments before detaching.</p>\n<p>The armor is able to filter the wearer's blood of certain substances to protect them from injury to a limited degree, such as by removing excess potassium resulting from muscle damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Quality/Flaws:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>SUPERIOR ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION:&nbsp;</strong>Protects the wearer from the harsh reality of their hostile envionment, or at least the most leathal aspects of shuch an environment - this effectively isolates the wearer from the atmospher, or lackthereof, around them. Basic Environment Protection is what's needed to be Vacuum Rated. Superior Environment Protection gives a +1 against environment-based Hazzard Checks.</p>\n<p><strong>FINE (Core Rules, pg 67)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>FOCUS ASSIST: DEXTERITY (FREEFALL): </strong>Equipping and using this item will grant the user a bonus to tests against the specified focus if they already have that focus, but does not otherwise confir any of the benefits of having the specified focus.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","weight":0,"cost":"18","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":4,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":4,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":-2,"isActive":true},"acc":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"str":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.9ULytiQl5lii7u7G"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.hW6Z6zrQHPU6uwr8"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/Task_Force_Police_officer_in_Sweden.png","effects":[]}
{"_id":"CXvVVlWruxKsLFsn","name":"Shield, Ballistic","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p>Ballistic Shield (Core Rules, pg 76)</p>\n<p>A larger and more heavy duty shield than a typical riot shield offering better protection. Like a riot shield, these too typically include a clear window the user can see through without exposing their head directly to the line of fire in which the shield has been deployed. Such gear is very effective against melee weapons as well as offering at least modest protection againsr most small arms. Wepons firing armor piercing rounds may be able to bypass such a shield however.</p>","weight":0,"cost":"14","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":3,"isActive":true},"impactArmor":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"ballisticArmor":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":null,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"str":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.CXvVVlWruxKsLFsn"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.n1MUcrWTGv9NE9yD"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/800px-Internal_troops_special_units_counter-terror_tactical_exercises_(38).jpeg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"GvkUmkdSoBvLMtyM","name":"Vac Suit - Belter","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<div title=\"Page 73\">\n<p><strong>Vac Suit (Core Rules, pg 71)</strong></p>\n<p>The primary characteristic that distinguises a belter vac suit from those more commonly seen in use by non-belters is the fairly mix-n-match approach to their maintenance and evolution resulting from the pragmatic belter approach to using whatever is available to get the job done. A typical belter vac suit has generally seen many years of service and may be a combination of parts that have been assembled from numerous sources over time.</p>\n<p>A vacuum suit, or as it's more commonly referred to - a vac suit, is an environmental protection suit able to sustain life in the harsh conditions of a hard vacuum such as that found in space. Such suits are in many ways like a tiny one-person space craft, though typically without any propulsion system. Nevertheless they have an environment control and protection system that will protect the wearer eaqually well in conditions ranging from full sun (extremely hot) to full darkness (extremely cold). Such a suit does not protect the wearer from exposure to a high radiation environment such as might occur durring a solar flare or in some other harsh working environments. Similarly exposure to a highly corrosive environment will likely degrade and break down the suit over time.</p>\n<p>Other systems that are typically built into a vac suit include a basic comms system, integrated mag boots, basic waste elimiantion system, a limited supply of food and water delivered to teh occupant through internal helmet mounted tubes, and at least rudimentary medical sensors (heart rate, respiration, body temp, etc.). More advanced models may also have correspondingly more sophisticated comms and medical diagnostic capabilities, as well the possibility to automatically adminsister some drugs to assist the occupant.</p>\n<p>Although these systems are necessarily complex, they're also designed and built to be easily repairable, and generally upgradeable. A properly cared for vac suit may last quite a long time, and so it's not unusual for such systems to be passed down from generation to generation in belter families.</p>\n<p><strong>Quality/Flaws</strong>:</p>\n<p><strong>BASIC ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION</strong>: Protects the wearer from the harsh reality of their hostile envionment, or at least the most leathal aspects of shuch an environment - this effectively isolates the wearer from the atmospher, or lackthereof, around them. Basic Environment Protection is what's needed to be Vacuum Rated. Superior Environment Protection gives a +1 against environment-based Hazzard Checks.</p>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":"11","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"str":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.GvkUmkdSoBvLMtyM"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.IZTRQg9BfwEln7ms"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/400px-Yastreb_space_suit_(MMA_2011)_(3).jpeg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"IVgMHmbldvHycQ2e","name":"Vac Suit","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<div title=\"Page 73\">\n<p><strong>Vac Suit (Core Rules, pg 71)</strong></p>\n<p>A vacuum suit, or as it's more commonly referred to - a vac suit, is an environmental protection suit able to sustain life in the harsh conditions of a hard vacuum such as that found in space. Such suits are in many ways like a tiny one-person space craft, though typically without any propulsion system. Nevertheless they have an environment control and protection system that will protect the wearer eaqually well in conditions ranging from full sun (extremely hot) to full darkness (extremely cold). Such a suit does not protect the wearer from exposure to a high radiation environment such as might occur durring a solar flare or in some other harsh working environments. Similarly exposure to a highly corrosive environment will likely degrade and break down the suit over time.</p>\n<p>Other systems that are typically built into a vac suit include a basic comms system, integrated mag boots, basic waste elimiantion system, a limited supply of food and water delivered to teh occupant through internal helmet mounted tubes, and at least rudimentary medical sensors (heart rate, respiration, body temp, etc.). More advanced models may also have correspondingly more sophisticated comms and medical diagnostic capabilities, as well the possibility to automatically adminsister some drugs to assist the occupant.</p>\n<p>Although these systems are necessarily complex, they're also designed and built to be easily repairable, and generally upgradeable. A properly cared for vac suit may last quite a long time, and so it's not unusual for such systems to be passed down from generation to generation in belter families.</p>\n<p><strong>Quality/Flaws</strong>:</p>\n<p><strong>BASIC ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION</strong>: Protects the wearer from the harsh reality of their hostile envionment, or at least the most leathal aspects of shuch an environment - this effectively isolates the wearer from the atmospher, or lackthereof, around them. Basic Environment Protection is what's needed to be Vacuum Rated. Superior Environment Protection gives a +1 against environment-based Hazzard Checks.</p>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":"13","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"str":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.IVgMHmbldvHycQ2e"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.D2zSNZGY6pj5LRQu"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/Gemini_Extravehicular_Space_Suit.jpeg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"JCO2KBLV9cWkNVSe","name":"Heavy Body Armor","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p><strong>Heavy Armor (Core Rules, pg 76)</strong></p>\n<p>This is the sort of armor modern soldiers typically go to war in. Far less protective or cappable than powered body armor, but also far less expensive - and so well suited for equiping the majority of combat soldiers.</p>\n<div title=\"Page 78\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Quality/Flaws</strong>:</p>\n</div>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">BASIC ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION</strong>: Protects the wearer from the harsh reality of their hostile envionment, or at least the most leathal aspects of shuch an environment - this effectively isolates the wearer from the atmospher, or lackthereof, around them. Basic Environment Protection is what's needed to be Vacuum Rated. Superior Environment Protection gives a +1 against Environment-Based Hazzard Checks.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div title=\"Page 78\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":"16","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":4,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":4,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive"