{"_id":"Ywe2HwaDbsQTDJ7a","name":"Emergency VAC-Suit DLP-025 Class E","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<div title=\"Page 73\">\n<p><strong>Emergency VAC-Suit DLP-025 Class E</strong></p>\n<p>The DLP-025 is an example of one of a miriad of cheap and readily available environmnet suits found in lockers near airlocks on any ship. Suits like this are manufactured to be just durable enough that in an emergency it will generally due, and are not at all suited for extended use. They somehow manage to be even less comforatable than a common vac suit - though obviously far superior to the alternative of not having a suit when you really need one.</p>\n<p><strong>See Environment Suits (Core Rules, pg 71)</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Quality/Flaws</strong>:</p>\n<p><strong>BASIC ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION</strong>: Protects the wearer from the harsh reality of their hostile envionment, or at least the most leathal aspects of shuch an environment - this effectively isolates the wearer from the atmospher, or lackthereof, around them. Basic Environment Protection is what's needed to be Vacuum Rated. Superior Environment Protection gives a +1 against environment-based Hazzard Checks.</p>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":"9","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive"