{"_id":"eicQyEEvIolARuRg","name":"Padding (Armor)","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p><strong>Padded Armor (Core Rules, pg 76)</strong></p>\n<div title=\"Page 78\">\n<p>Padded armor is the least encumbering armor that can be worn and still constitute armor.</p>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":"8","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":null,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"str":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.eicQyEEvIolARuRg"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.r2GHvRti5SAqRwy3"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/M69_2_whiteBG.jpeg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"j4iYYrp0ghWW4DLs","name":"Powered Armor","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p><strong>Powered Armor (Core Rules, pg 76)</strong></p>\n<div title=\"Page 79\">\n<p>One of the most fearsome sights on the battlefield is military power armor, like the Goliath suits worn by Martian Marines. Two and a half meters tall and weighing 400 kilograms even before a soldier climbs inside, power armor provides both a formidable offense and defense.</p>\n<p>Half armor and half spacesuit, the armor has radiation shielding sufficient to let soldiers walk through a nuclear bomb crater minutes after the blast. The armor&rsquo;s titanium and ceramic-composite exterior shielding is typically painted with camouflage patterns appropriate to the assignment, and enemies are often surprised just how well an enormous soldier in power armor can blend into the environment when they stand still. The armor&rsquo;s hydraulics system magnifies the wearer&rsquo;s strength, much like a mech rig, and carries most of the weight of the suit, allowing soldiers in power armor to undertake marathon hikes and move surprisingly fast. They also enable the armor to carry heavy weaponry, typically a rotary machine gun and sometimes a grenade launcher or micro-missile pack.</p>\n<p>Sensor packages feed data to the wearer on the helmet&rsquo;s HUD, allowing them to identify and track infrared targeting lasers used by opponents&rsquo; weapons, and even visually parse those weapons using the suit&rsquo;s camera feeds to match them against an internal database. Those same cameras monitor in all directions, sending feeds back to squad officers and their military command center, which can monitor the life signs of both the soldiers and opponents who have been detected and attacked.</p>\n<p>Despite all these capabilities, power armor is still designed for maneuverability in tight spaces, enabling infantry to move in microgravity and storm their way through the narrow confines of ships. Less so is a newer addition to the Martian arsenal: 4-meter tall, 9-ton combat mechs, walking tanks carrying rail guns and missiles adapted from ship weapon systems. They are strictly ground-assault troops, and there are few installations or opponents able to stand against them for long.</p>\n<p><strong>Qualities/Flaws:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>ARMOR</strong>: +12 armor bonus with no armor penalty while operational.</p>\n<p><strong>PHYSICAL ENHANCEMENT</strong>: +10 bonus to Strength and Strength (Might) tests.</p>\n<p><strong>MOBILITY ENHANCEMENT:</strong> +2 bonus to Speed. +4 bonus to Constitution (Endurance) tests.</p>\n<p><strong>WEAPONRY</strong>: An integral rifle doing 3d6 + Perception damage and capable of performing automatic weapon gun stunts. May also have grenade or missile systems doing 3d6 damage in a 5 meter radius.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 79\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>CAMOFLAGE PACKAGE</strong>: +2 bonus to Dexterity (Stealth) tests compatible with the unit&rsquo;s camouflage.</p>\n<p><strong>SENSORS</strong>: +2 bonus to Perception tests where the armor&rsquo;s sensor package applies.</p>\n<p><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">BASIC ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION</strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">: Protects the wearer from the harsh reality of their hostile envionment, or at least the most leathal aspects of shuch an environment - this effectively isolates the wearer from the atmospher, or lackthereof, around them. Basic Environment Protection is what's needed to be Vacuum Rated. Superior Environment Protection gives a +1 against environment-based Hazzard Checks.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 79\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":"*","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":12,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":12,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"str":{"value":10,"isActive":true},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.j4iYYrp0ghWW4DLs"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.3w7mZ5GYRUGOM2q8"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/rock-golem.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"mNjHkMTNWUtUFSoc","name":"Light Body Armor","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p><strong>Light Body Armor&nbsp;(Core Rules, pg 76)</strong></p>\n<p>At the lower end of the rage of body armor in terms of protective capabilty this sort of body armor is readily available, relatively inexpensive, and commonly employed by police and security forces who are not expecting to encounter a well armed opponent. This sort of armor is much more comfortable than other options and imposes only a minor reduction to speed or mobility. Armor like this may be worn under ordinary clothes, but will probably be noticable as such given it's bulk.</p>","weight":0,"cost":"12","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":null,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"str":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.mNjHkMTNWUtUFSoc"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.wiv5oleQymIzsz1r"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/NIJ_LVLIIIA_Kogelvrij_vest%2C_BA8001.jpeg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"oMgQ64ka6UsNY6yc","name":"Powered Armor - Reaver","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p><strong>Powered Armor (Core Rules, pg 76)</strong></p>\n<div title=\"Page 79\">\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\">One of the most fearsome sights on the battlefield is military power armor, like the Goliath suits worn by Martian Marines. Two and a half meters tall and weighing 400 kilograms even before a soldier climbs inside, power armor provides both a formidable offense and defense.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\">Half armor and half spacesuit, the armor has radiation shielding sufficient to let soldiers walk through a nuclear bomb crater minutes after the blast. The armor&rsquo;s titanium and ceramic-composite exterior shielding is typically painted with camouflage patterns appropriate to the assignment, and enemies are often surprised just how well an enormous soldier in power armor can blend into the environment when they stand still. The armor&rsquo;s hydraulics system magnifies the wearer&rsquo;s strength, much like a mech rig, and carries most of the weight of the suit, allowing soldiers in power armor to undertake marathon hikes and move surprisingly fast. They also enable the armor to carry heavy weaponry, typically a rotary machine gun and sometimes a grenade launcher or micro-missile pack.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\">Sensor packages feed data to the wearer on the helmet&rsquo;s HUD, allowing them to identify and track infrared targeting lasers used by opponents&rsquo; weapons, and even visually parse those weapons using the suit&rsquo;s camera feeds to match them against an internal database. Those same cameras monitor in all directions, sending feeds back to squad officers and their military command center, which can monitor the life signs of both the soldiers and opponents who have been detected and attacked.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\">Despite all these capabilities, power armor is still designed for maneuverability in tight spaces, enabling infantry to move in microgravity and storm their way through the narrow confines of ships. Less so is a newer addition to the Martian arsenal: 4-meter tall, 9-ton combat mechs, walking tanks carrying rail guns and missiles adapted from ship weapon systems. They are strictly ground-assault troops, and there are few installations or opponents able to stand against them for long.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong>Reaver Power Armor</strong></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong>Reaver Powered Armor</strong> is a Powered armor suit utilized by the United Nations Marine Corps for combat scenarios. These suits are resistant to most small arms.</p>\n<p><strong>Qualities/Flaws:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>ARMOR</strong>: +12 armor bonus with no armor penalty while operational.</p>\n<p><strong>PHYSICAL ENHANCEMENT</strong>: +10 effective bonus to Strength and Strength(Might) tests.</p>\n<p><strong>MOBILITY ENHANCEMENT:</strong> +2 bonus to Speed. +4 bonus to Constitution (Endurance) tests.</p>\n<p><strong>WEAPONRY</strong>: An integral rifle doing 3d6 + Perception damage and capable of performing automatic weapon gun stunts. May also have grenade or missile systems doing 3d6 damage in a 5 meter radius.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 79\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%