{"_id":"pG3RBVmBshlFDUfZ","name":"Advanced Light Body Armor","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong>Adanced light armor</strong></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\">This armor is made from a special kevlar weave infused with a rapid hardening ballistic gel which enables the armor to respond to a blow by making itself temporarily rigid wherever it's been hit without otheriwse encombering the wearer. It's sufficiently light to wear under a loose shirt or jacket such that the wearer will not appear to be armored unless carfully examined.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong>See Light Armor (Core Rules, pg )</strong></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Qualities/Flaws:</strong></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps; background-color: #ffffff;\"><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">LIGHT</strong>: (<strong>Core Rules, pg 67)</strong></p>","weight":0,"cost":"12","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":1,"isActive":true},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":null,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"str":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.pG3RBVmBshlFDUfZ"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.gHo2RKo3gIf9d24x"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/abdominal-armor.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"r97m7rkOFYrr9Ewn","name":"Powered Armor - Goliath","permission":{"default":0,"wypGoDpbSltPFEBU":3},"type":"equipment","data":{"shortDesc":"","longDesc":"<p><strong>Powered Armor (Core Rules, pg 76)</strong></p>\n<div title=\"Page 79\">\n<p>One of the most fearsome sights on the battlefield is military power armor, like the Goliath suits worn by Martian Marines. Two and a half meters tall and weighing 400 kilograms even before a soldier climbs inside, power armor provides both a formidable offense and defense.</p>\n<p>Half armor and half spacesuit, the armor has radiation shielding sufficient to let soldiers walk through a nuclear bomb crater minutes after the blast. The armor&rsquo;s titanium and ceramic-composite exterior shielding is typically painted with camouflage patterns appropriate to the assignment, and enemies are often surprised just how well an enormous soldier in power armor can blend into the environment when they stand still. The armor&rsquo;s hydraulics system magnifies the wearer&rsquo;s strength, much like a mech rig, and carries most of the weight of the suit, allowing soldiers in power armor to undertake marathon hikes and move surprisingly fast. They also enable the armor to carry heavy weaponry, typically a rotary machine gun and sometimes a grenade launcher or micro-missile pack.</p>\n<p>Sensor packages feed data to the wearer on the helmet&rsquo;s HUD, allowing them to identify and track infrared targeting lasers used by opponents&rsquo; weapons, and even visually parse those weapons using the suit&rsquo;s camera feeds to match them against an internal database. Those same cameras monitor in all directions, sending feeds back to squad officers and their military command center, which can monitor the life signs of both the soldiers and opponents who have been detected and attacked.</p>\n<p>Despite all these capabilities, power armor is still designed for maneuverability in tight spaces, enabling infantry to move in microgravity and storm their way through the narrow confines of ships. Less so is a newer addition to the Martian arsenal: 4-meter tall, 9-ton combat mechs, walking tanks carrying rail guns and missiles adapted from ship weapon systems. They are strictly ground-assault troops, and there are few installations or opponents able to stand against them for long.</p>\n<p>Goliath Powered Armor worn by the Martian Marine Corps&nbsp;Force Recon Marines is designed to let Marines walk through a nuclear explosion crater minutes after the blast. The HUD, which can be controlled through blinks and eye movements, can show information ranging from maps and combat information to suit diagnostics. It also included a gun built into the right arm. Squad leaders are even able to view their squad's life signs and equipment status reports.</p>\n<p>Goliath armor utilizes an inbuilt multibarrel minigun firing armor-piercing, high-explosive, and 6.25mm incendiary-tipped caseless ammunition. Inbuilt RPGs (Rocket Propelled Grenades) have also been shown to be worn within the back of the armor and can be remotely targeted. Grenades are also used by Marines in this armor and can be attached directly onto the armor exterior for storage. The inbuilt weapons onboard Goliath armor are DNA encoded and cannot be operated by anyone but the assigned Marine user.</p>\n<p>Most small arms used on ships are incapable of penetrating the armor of these suits as they are designed not to penetrate the hull of ships exposing the interiors to vacuum by gunfire. In spite of this, a skilled sharpshooter can obtain an accurate kill against this armor by targeting points in the faceplate.</p>\n<h4><strong>Goliath Mark I/II&nbsp;(presumed)</strong></h4>\n<p>The early variants of vacuum-rated Goliath armor. This armor had a solid metal chest piece unlike later models.</p>\n<h4><strong>Goliath Mark III</strong></h4>\n<p>This Mark of armor is visibly different from its predecessor with a redesigned chest piece and more sleek shoulder armor. Two lights are visible on the chest armor. The Mark III would be the basis for later Marks.</p>\n<h4><strong>Goliath Mark IV</strong></h4>\n<p>At the time of the Ganymede Incident the Mark IV; powered armor suit was the main suit in use by the Martian Marine Corps. Although lacking any visible differences to the previous model, the Mark IV; has a completely reworked firmware incompatible with earlier Marks; suits.</p>\n<h4><strong>Goliath Mark V</strong></h4>\n<p>In use by the time of the Slow Zone Incident. Marine Jed Trepp&nbsp;wore Mark V;&nbsp;The Mark externally was the same in design as the two previous Marks.</p>\n<p><strong>Qualities/Flaws:</strong></p>\n<p><strong>ARMOR</strong>: +12 armor bonus with no armor penalty while operational.</p>\n<p><strong>PHYSICAL ENHANCEMENT</strong>: +10 effective bonus to Strength and Strength (Might) tests.</p>\n<p><strong>MOBILITY ENHANCEMENT:</strong> +2 bonus to Speed. +4 bonus to Constitution (Endurance) tests.</p>\n<p><strong>WEAPONRY</strong>: An integral rifle doing 3d6 + Perception damage and capable of performing automatic weapon gun stunts. May also have grenade or missile systems doing 3d6 damage in a 5 meter radius.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 79\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><strong>CAMOFLAGE PACKAGE</strong>: +2 bonus to Dexterity (Stealth) tests compatible with the unit&rsquo;s camouflage.</p>\n<p><strong>SENSORS</strong>: +2 bonus to Perception tests where the armor&rsquo;s sensor package applies.</p>\n<p><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">BASIC ENVIRONMENT PROTECTION</strong><span style=\"color: #191813; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\">: Protects the wearer from the harsh reality of their hostile envionment, or at least the most leathal aspects of shuch an environment - this effectively isolates the wearer from the atmospher, or lackthereof, around them. Basic Environment Protection is what's needed to be Vacuum Rated. Superior Environment Protection gives a +1 against environment-based Hazzard Checks.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 79\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","weight":0,"cost":"*","quantity":1,"equiped":false,"itemMods":{"itemDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"actorDamage":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"itemActivation":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"focus":{"name":"","value":0,"isActive":false},"defense":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"impactArmor":{"value":12,"isActive":true},"ballisticArmor":{"value":12,"isActive":true},"toughness":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"speed":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"defendMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"guardupMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"allOutAtkMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxHealth":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxConviction":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"maxPowerPoints":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"powerForce":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"aimMnv":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"armorPenalty":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"acc":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"comm":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cons":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"cunn":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"dex":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"fight":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"int":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"magic":{"value":0,"isActive":false},"per":{"value":2,"isActive":true},"str":{"value":10,"isActive":true},"will":{"value":0,"isActive":false}}},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.expanse-gear-pack.armor.r97m7rkOFYrr9Ewn"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.xy4mD5bLGznHrMWt"}},"img":"modules/expanse-gear-pack/item-assets/armor/rock-golem.svg","effects":[]}
